-- Air France says to sell 2.2 percent stake in Amadeus 
-- By Sarah Morris
-- Tue Nov 25, 2014 01:44PM EST
-- None



MADRID, Nov 25 (Reuters) - Air France <AIRF.PA> said on Tuesday it is selling a 2.2 percent stake in Spanish travel technology company Amadeus <AMA.MC> through a derivatives deal with Deutsche Bank.

Air France said it will own about 2.2 percent of Amadeus following the deal and has committed to a 30-day lock up period on the remaining stake.